\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Independent Institute of Education \'28Pty\'29 Ltd is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education institution\'2C and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC. \line \line The institution has also applied for a Higher Certificate in Skin and Body Therapy. \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that Criteria 1\'2C 3 and 7 do not comply with minimum standards. \line In terms of Criterion 1\'2C the evaluator argues that the programme conceptualization and design is flawed. The evaluator noted that there is a distinct difference between cosmetology and skin and body therapy. There are 4 subjects related to Business. A total of 56 credits is assigned to these business modules\'2C which the evaluator considers to be too high for this programme and its related qualifier. In view of this\'2C the programme does not match the CESM category in which it has been placed. Subjects such as Anatomy and Physiology and Nutrition are combined and are assigned lower credit allocations. The rules for these combinations are unclear. The programme guide also indicates that these subjects will be offered in one semester. The time allocation for these modules is considered to be insufficient. In order to conduct advanced therapies\'2C a sound understanding of anatomy and physiology is needed together with fundamental science components \'28for example\'3A To conduct advanced therapies using machinery these fundamental elements of knowledge are required\'29. Nail technology is not an advanced therapy and this should not be at the denoted level. The evaluator also emphasizes that in the purpose of this qualification\'2C emphasis should be placed on client analysis \'28recognizing specific disorders or pathologies\'2C referral where necessary etc\'2C\'29 rather than a critical analysis of the business. It is important to note that in a health\'E2\'80\'93related programme students must be taught how to conduct professional treatments in an ethically sound manner.\line The proposed programme makes provision for work integrated learning for which there is said to be \'E2\'80\'9Cshared responsibility\'E2\'80\'9D. It appears however that the WIL reponsibilty rests heavily on the students - they find their own salons to visit and book their own clients for salon days. The evaluator suggests that the programme must take responsibility for the management of this process in order to ensure that the quality is not compromised and the work done aligns with the outcomes of the course \'28ie\'3A purpose\'29. \line The staffing complement is also judged not to comply with minimum standards. All the staffmembers teaching on the proposed qualification are part-time\'2C therefore there are no core full-time staff members. This is unsuitable for the purpose of teaching and learning. These staff members will not be available for regular consultation. In addition\'2C the HOD is not a subject matter expert which adds to the concern regarding academic leadership and support. Concerns raised in terms of the staffing at the various sites proposed for offering the programme include\'3A\line 1. Cape Town\line - There are only two staff members with qualifications in the field. Both of these staff members have less than 3 years\'27 teaching experience.\line - These staff members teach modules directly related to the qualifier\line 2. Johannesburg\line - Only 1 staff member is qualified in the field.\line - Though she has 7 years\'27 teaching experience\'2C she will be the only staff member teaching modules directly related to the qualifier \'28together with all the practicals\'29.\line - As a part-time staff member it cannot be possible that she will be able to manage this in a manner that is conducive to teaching and learning and that supports student needs.\line 3. Pretoria\line - The total number of staff is 3- all part-time.\line - Only 1 staff member is qualified in the field and she has only 1 year of teaching experience.\line \line The evaluator concluded that it is evident that the current staffing portfolio does not meet the needs of a vocational programme of this nature.\line In terms of Criterion 7 the evaluator indicated that there was a lack of adequate information to determine whether the various sites have the required infrastructure and resources to offer the programme.\line \line The Directorate supports the recommendation that the programme should not be accredited. \line \cell \pard 

